1
00:00:15,715 --> 00:00:17,740
- No, I didn't.
- Yes, you did.

2
00:00:17,817 --> 00:00:19,478
- I did not!
- Yes, you did.

3
00:00:19,552 --> 00:00:21,952
Just let me play with it.
Come on, you promised.

4
00:00:22,022 --> 00:00:23,512
- No, I didn't.
- Yes, you did.

5
00:00:23,590 --> 00:00:25,217
- I did not!
- Yes, you did...

6
00:00:28,061 --> 00:00:29,494
What's the problem?

7
00:00:29,562 --> 00:00:31,553
- Nothing.
- Then chill out.

8
00:00:32,799 --> 00:00:35,324
Dad, he promised to let me play with it.

9
00:00:35,502 --> 00:00:37,868
And now he says he didn't, and he won't.

10
00:00:42,275 --> 00:00:43,606
Did you?

11
00:00:43,877 --> 00:00:46,107
- Did I what?
- Did you promise?

12
00:00:47,180 --> 00:00:49,080
Yeah, but no big deal.

13
00:00:49,816 --> 00:00:51,374
Yes, it is.

14
00:00:52,485 --> 00:00:53,952
Yes, it is a big deal.

15
00:00:54,020 --> 00:00:57,683
You can't just say, "I promise,"
and then forget about it.

16
00:00:58,591 --> 00:01:02,220
"I promise" are the most important words
you'll ever say.

17
00:01:02,495 --> 00:01:05,658
Well, almost the most important words
you'll ever say.

18
00:01:07,634 --> 00:01:10,933
- You know what I mean?
- No, why?

19
00:01:13,173 --> 00:01:15,141
Because I say so, that's why.

20
00:01:16,209 --> 00:01:19,736
No, because it only takes a second
to say "I promise"...

21
00:01:20,013 --> 00:01:23,210
but the commitment could last
the rest of your life.

22
00:01:39,232 --> 00:01:43,965
Remember I told you guys about
Uncle Bobby and me when we were kids?

23
00:01:44,237 --> 00:01:45,397
- Yeah.
- Of course.

24
00:01:45,472 --> 00:01:48,305
I didn't tell you the whole story because...

25
00:01:48,608 --> 00:01:52,601
I left out a bunch of stuff
because I figured you guys were too young.

26
00:01:53,213 --> 00:01:56,148
Well, I guess now is as good a time as any.

27
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:03,484
In fact, now is just about perfect. Okay.

28
00:02:06,493 --> 00:02:10,190
All right, listen up.
But I want you to remember something:

29
00:02:11,831 --> 00:02:14,664
History is all in the mind of the teller.

30
00:02:15,802 --> 00:02:17,963
Truth is all in the telling.

31
00:02:22,008 --> 00:02:23,407
Understand?

32
00:02:24,177 --> 00:02:25,576
Not really.

33
00:02:27,514 --> 00:02:29,505
Don't worry about it. You will.

34
00:02:31,017 --> 00:02:32,746
To understand the whole thing...

35
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:35,879
to understand why a promise
is such a big and important deal...

36
00:02:35,955 --> 00:02:38,082
you gotta go back...

37
00:02:38,791 --> 00:02:42,022
to before any of it ever happened.

38
00:02:44,497 --> 00:02:48,797
<i>Back to before we ever lived in Novato,</i>
<i>before we even came to California. </i>

39
00:02:49,569 --> 00:02:51,901
<i>Back even before we were born. </i>

40
00:02:55,708 --> 00:02:56,766
Go ahead.

41
00:02:56,843 --> 00:03:00,438
<i>You have to go way back</i>
<i>to a kid named Fisher... </i>

42
00:03:01,281 --> 00:03:03,715
<i>who wanted to be a legend. </i>

43
00:03:04,784 --> 00:03:06,911
Come on, guys. We're almost there.

44
00:03:09,789 --> 00:03:11,450
Careful, all right?

45
00:03:11,524 --> 00:03:14,084
- Hold it steady.
- I got it.

46
00:03:30,843 --> 00:03:32,868
Fisher, it can't be done!

47
00:03:34,347 --> 00:03:37,441
- It can be done.
- No, it can't, God damn it!

48
00:03:37,650 --> 00:03:40,016
It's far as a football field to that fence!

49
00:03:40,086 --> 00:03:42,486
Come on, Fish, listen to us.
We're your friends!

50
00:03:42,555 --> 00:03:45,046
This is nuts, Fish. You're gonna get hurt.

51
00:03:45,258 --> 00:03:46,919
- Don't do this.
- Cape.

52
00:03:47,594 --> 00:03:50,324
Come on, keep it steady.
Don't let it fall, okay?

53
00:03:50,396 --> 00:03:51,693
He's not gonna listen.

54
00:03:58,104 --> 00:04:00,038
<i>That's exactly how Fisher got remembered:</i>

55
00:04:01,274 --> 00:04:02,332
Flag it!

56
00:04:02,408 --> 00:04:03,807
<i>... as a legend. </i>

57
00:04:04,544 --> 00:04:07,911
<i>Ten years later,</i>
<i>when we finally got to California... </i>

58
00:04:08,348 --> 00:04:11,715
<i>his legend would change our lives forever. </i>

59
00:04:13,519 --> 00:04:14,986
Careful, man!

60
00:04:16,356 --> 00:04:18,449
- Watch out!
- God, what have we done?

61
00:05:02,869 --> 00:05:04,234
Oh, my God!

62
00:05:22,388 --> 00:05:24,913
- Hang on, Fish!
- We're coming for you!

63
00:05:28,227 --> 00:05:30,491
Oh, man! He's...

64
00:05:33,266 --> 00:05:34,426
Alive!

65
00:05:36,235 --> 00:05:38,430
- Your leg.
- It's twisted.

66
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:40,305
Don't touch me!

67
00:05:40,373 --> 00:05:42,671
You did it, man! You flew!

68
00:05:42,975 --> 00:05:44,636
All right, Fish!

69
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:48,974
- You did it.
- I did it.

70
00:05:55,555 --> 00:05:57,250
I really flew.

71
00:06:08,835 --> 00:06:12,271
Bobby, close the window.
You've been flying for three hours.

72
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:17,300
- But I like the wind.
- Yes, I know you do.

73
00:06:20,046 --> 00:06:21,138
Yuck.

74
00:06:24,317 --> 00:06:26,547
It's my scoop. You had the last one.

75
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:29,220
But that is the last one.

76
00:06:29,389 --> 00:06:32,483
Okay, we'll share it. Fifty-fifty. Here.

77
00:06:33,025 --> 00:06:37,155
<i>One day, before the long trip,</i>
<i>our dad didn't come home. </i>

78
00:06:38,131 --> 00:06:41,294
<i>Our mom knew why, but she never told us</i>
<i>and we never asked her... </i>

79
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:43,892
<i>because we knew it made her sad. </i>

80
00:06:46,339 --> 00:06:49,206
That's eight jars, Mom. How far is that?

81
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:52,878
- Mom?
- What?

82
00:06:52,945 --> 00:06:54,913
How far is that, eight jars?

83
00:06:56,816 --> 00:06:59,649
I don't know. You have to check it out.

84
00:07:01,621 --> 00:07:03,816
1,500 miles.

85
00:07:03,890 --> 00:07:07,621
- Does it snow in California?
- No. It doesn't rain, either.

86
00:07:09,295 --> 00:07:10,455
Thank you.

87
00:07:12,398 --> 00:07:14,866
<i>Mom had waited three months</i>
<i>for him to come back. </i>

88
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:18,870
<i>When she was pretty sure he wasn't,</i>
<i>she packed everything we had in our car... </i>

89
00:07:18,938 --> 00:07:22,066
<i>and told us we were going West</i>
<i>for a fresh start. </i>

90
00:07:26,212 --> 00:07:30,876
<i>Our dad was never around much anyway,</i>
<i>so after those first 1,500 miles... </i>

91
00:07:31,851 --> 00:07:34,547
<i>me and Bobby just forgot all about him. </i>

92
00:07:34,754 --> 00:07:36,915
<i>And Mom, well... </i>

93
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:39,584
<i>Mom pretended like she did. </i>

94
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:43,987
<i>By that time,</i>
<i>I knew that I would never see him again... </i>

95
00:07:44,597 --> 00:07:47,293
<i>and that now I was the man of the family. </i>

96
00:07:48,234 --> 00:07:51,362
Go west, young mom. Go right, Mom.

97
00:07:57,076 --> 00:08:00,603
- Bobby. It's lethal.
- I didn't do it.

98
00:08:02,081 --> 00:08:05,107
- Mikey!
- Wait a minute. I didn't do it.

99
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:11,483
It's that dog. It's deadly! Come on.

100
00:08:11,557 --> 00:08:14,617
- Get out of here.
- Come on.

101
00:08:17,897 --> 00:08:19,956
It doesn't help that much.

102
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:31,207
"Want to know more about the Old West?

103
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:35,037
"Exit one-half mile ahead to see the best.

104
00:08:35,114 --> 00:08:38,606
"Just mosey on in Geronimo Bill's
Buffalo Farm and Wild West Adventure. "

105
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:40,015
Can we go, Mom? Please!

106
00:08:42,755 --> 00:08:45,155
<i>Except for the giant dinosaur in Missouri... </i>

107
00:08:45,224 --> 00:08:48,421
<i>that they had turned into a hamburger stand</i>
<i>when it died... </i>

108
00:08:48,494 --> 00:08:53,022
<i>what we saw in Oklahoma</i>
<i>was the greatest thing we'd ever seen. </i>

109
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:55,995
Thanks a lot, Mom.

110
00:08:56,903 --> 00:09:00,805
- Can we please stay the whole day?
- Yeah, please?

111
00:09:00,873 --> 00:09:04,570
- How many buffalo do you think they have?
- I bet there's millions.

112
00:09:12,385 --> 00:09:14,945
Keep your eye on that dog, Eugene.

113
00:09:18,024 --> 00:09:19,924
- Hi, boys.
- Hi.

114
00:09:19,992 --> 00:09:22,586
Welcome to
the Geronimo Bill Buffalo Farm...

115
00:09:22,662 --> 00:09:25,096
and Wild Adventure Souvenir Shop.

116
00:09:26,666 --> 00:09:29,362
That'll be three for 75¢, ma'am.

117
00:09:32,004 --> 00:09:36,941
Would it be okay if I just set them up
on the fence so they could see the buffalo?

118
00:09:40,012 --> 00:09:42,640
Well, ma'am, today is your lucky day.

119
00:09:42,882 --> 00:09:46,443
You see, it's Free Admission Day
for all folks from out of town.

120
00:09:46,519 --> 00:09:48,453
Hey, we're from Jersey.

121
00:09:49,188 --> 00:09:51,281
That don't make y'all bad.

122
00:09:53,826 --> 00:09:57,455
So you go on in,
stick to the path, and enjoy yourself.

123
00:09:59,165 --> 00:10:01,656
- All right!
- Man, look at that.

124
00:10:04,003 --> 00:10:06,335
Come on. Mom can't afford that.

125
00:10:06,906 --> 00:10:09,340
- Thanks a lot.
- Thanks for coming.

126
00:10:15,548 --> 00:10:18,517
Okay, troops. Keep your eyes on the buffalo.

127
00:10:19,485 --> 00:10:21,544
- Go ahead, Mom.
- Thank you.

128
00:10:25,191 --> 00:10:27,921
Don't let your dog get my buffalo, son.

129
00:10:30,062 --> 00:10:31,427
Thank you.

130
00:10:40,206 --> 00:10:42,174
Wow! Look at...

131
00:10:44,810 --> 00:10:46,141
He's huge.

132
00:10:47,146 --> 00:10:48,670
He's huge, Mom.

133
00:10:49,215 --> 00:10:52,275
- Bobby, look at him.
- Isn't he beautiful?

134
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:55,710
Look at that.

135
00:10:56,322 --> 00:10:58,552
But where are the other ones?

136
00:10:59,625 --> 00:11:02,492
Think he's the only buffalo left in the world?

137
00:11:02,561 --> 00:11:03,892
Maybe he is.

138
00:11:09,135 --> 00:11:10,659
Oh, gosh, Mom.

139
00:11:11,203 --> 00:11:13,637
- He looks lonely.
- I'm sure he is.

140
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:16,868
Mom, what's gonna happen to him?

141
00:11:18,377 --> 00:11:21,005
- It's so sad.
- Why?

142
00:11:21,414 --> 00:11:25,544
I don't know, Mikey. I guess
that's what happens when you're alone.

143
00:11:28,421 --> 00:11:30,821
There's lots more to see. Come on.

144
00:11:44,437 --> 00:11:47,372
You boys take care of your mom now,
you hear?

145
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:49,271
<i>We promised we would. </i>

146
00:11:49,942 --> 00:11:52,035
<i>We never broke that promise. </i>

147
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:48,859
Fuck.

148
00:12:51,103 --> 00:12:53,094
I'm sorry.

149
00:12:53,572 --> 00:12:55,870
I didn't mean... It was an accident.

150
00:12:56,742 --> 00:12:59,734
Somebody give me some soap.
I'll do it myself.

151
00:13:02,715 --> 00:13:07,084
<i>Finally, after 22 jars of peanut butter,</i>
<i>and just as Mom ran out of money... </i>

152
00:13:07,153 --> 00:13:10,281
<i>we made it to the apartment</i>
<i>of an aunt we didn't even know we had. </i>

153
00:13:10,356 --> 00:13:12,347
- I'm driving.
- It's too low, Mom.

154
00:13:12,424 --> 00:13:16,121
- It's not too low.
- Yes, it is. Not that one. This one.

155
00:13:19,665 --> 00:13:22,691
Michael, I told you to tie it on tighter.

156
00:13:28,207 --> 00:13:29,868
You broke my bike!

157
00:13:30,376 --> 00:13:32,901
Oh, my God, they're here! Mary!

158
00:13:34,079 --> 00:13:36,445
Lois, hi! How are you?

159
00:13:36,515 --> 00:13:38,676
You got here. Bill, honey, they're here.

160
00:13:38,751 --> 00:13:41,618
This is Bobby and this is Mikey!

161
00:13:41,687 --> 00:13:43,416
- Hi, Bobby.
- How you doing?

162
00:13:43,489 --> 00:13:45,150
- Mikey.
- Who's the dog?

163
00:13:45,224 --> 00:13:48,421
And this is Shane.
Don't worry, he's housebroken.

164
00:13:49,195 --> 00:13:50,492
- But they're not.
- Mom!

165
00:13:55,034 --> 00:13:57,867
<i>As it turned out,</i>
<i>we didn't have to stay there too long... </i>

166
00:13:57,937 --> 00:14:01,839
<i>because about a month after we got there,</i>
<i>he entered our lives. </i>

167
00:14:03,943 --> 00:14:05,274
Oh, Jack.

168
00:14:06,812 --> 00:14:08,712
<i>Mom liked him right away. </i>

169
00:14:09,381 --> 00:14:11,212
<i>After she'd known him for a while... </i>

170
00:14:11,283 --> 00:14:13,683
<i>she said that he was the answer</i>
<i>to all her prayers. </i>

171
00:14:13,752 --> 00:14:17,051
I want those two top cards. Keep me in.

172
00:14:17,156 --> 00:14:19,624
You guys remember what I told you.
Cover up.

173
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:21,353
- Okay.
- All right.

174
00:14:29,201 --> 00:14:33,661
<i>We called him The King,</i>
<i>because that's what he liked to be called. </i>

175
00:14:34,206 --> 00:14:35,969
- Here's a cold one.
- Thanks, Mom.

176
00:14:36,041 --> 00:14:39,499
- That looks good.
- He's fixing the bike you broke, Mom.

177
00:14:40,913 --> 00:14:43,473
Come on, Bobby, blow! Make a wish!

178
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:46,643
- Come on, sweetheart.
- Blow, Bobby.

179
00:14:47,319 --> 00:14:48,980
All right, Bobby!

180
00:14:57,329 --> 00:14:59,388
Wow, a Radio Flyer!

181
00:14:59,665 --> 00:15:01,462
- Wow.
- Do you like it?

182
00:15:01,667 --> 00:15:03,794
- Yeah, thanks, Mom.
- You do?

183
00:15:03,869 --> 00:15:05,928
- I thought you would like it.
- I love it.

184
00:15:07,006 --> 00:15:08,906
Happy birthday, Bobby.

185
00:15:37,036 --> 00:15:40,199
<i>It was at a carnival where, for the first time... </i>

186
00:15:40,806 --> 00:15:44,298
<i>I knew there was something different</i>
<i>about my brother. </i>

187
00:15:45,511 --> 00:15:49,413
<i>I could tell by the look in his eyes that night</i>
<i>that he knew... </i>

188
00:15:49,648 --> 00:15:54,381
<i>about a special, secret thing</i>
<i>that all kids know. </i>

189
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:56,620
<i>Only, he knew more. </i>

190
00:15:57,756 --> 00:15:59,280
<i>A lot more. </i>

191
00:16:09,101 --> 00:16:11,535
Here you go. Yeah, that's right.

192
00:16:11,870 --> 00:16:14,202
Okay, look. See this? You close that up.

193
00:16:14,273 --> 00:16:17,037
- It's just like a safety pin.
- That's it.

194
00:16:17,676 --> 00:16:20,770
Okay, pick that up.
Let me cast it out there for you.

195
00:16:20,846 --> 00:16:25,340
You wanna bring it back.
Let it go at about one o'clock. Bingo!

196
00:16:26,518 --> 00:16:27,746
That was far.

197
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:29,720
- Not bad, huh?
- That's a good cast.

198
00:16:29,788 --> 00:16:31,380
Here you go. Whose turn is it?

199
00:16:31,457 --> 00:16:33,550
- It's Bobby's.
- Okay, here you go.

200
00:16:33,625 --> 00:16:36,753
- Here we go. You're gonna catch a big one.
- All right.

201
00:16:40,332 --> 00:16:42,766
Reel it in, but don't pull too hard now.

202
00:16:58,684 --> 00:17:01,118
- You got one!
- I got one!

203
00:17:01,186 --> 00:17:03,620
- Wow!
- Reel it in!

204
00:17:03,756 --> 00:17:06,122
Come on, hurry. Push it and pull.

205
00:17:06,191 --> 00:17:08,557
- It's a honker!
- Reel it in slow. Nice and easy.

206
00:17:08,627 --> 00:17:11,221
- Don't pull too hard.
- I got it.

207
00:17:11,296 --> 00:17:13,093
- Easy.
- Come on, reel it in.

208
00:17:13,165 --> 00:17:16,794
- Reel it in. Here.
- Reel it in nice and easy. Come on!

209
00:17:16,935 --> 00:17:19,995
- Don't pull so hard. You bent it too much.
- Darn.

210
00:17:20,606 --> 00:17:22,335
God damn it, Bobby!

211
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:28,711
What the hell's the matter with you?
I told you not to pull so hard, didn't I?

212
00:17:29,548 --> 00:17:32,073
What's the matter? You deaf or just stupid?

213
00:17:32,184 --> 00:17:34,846
Hey, I'm talking to you. Listen to me.

214
00:17:35,587 --> 00:17:39,421
Knock it off, or I'll really give you
something to cry about.

215
00:17:39,691 --> 00:17:42,285
That was a $5 lure, for Christ's sake.

216
00:17:55,407 --> 00:17:58,376
All right. Here.

217
00:18:00,679 --> 00:18:02,408
Here, use mine.

218
00:18:02,714 --> 00:18:05,615
I'll set you up with a new lure on this one.

219
00:18:05,684 --> 00:18:08,517
Remember, the good fish wait for no man,
all right?

220
00:18:11,423 --> 00:18:13,857
<i>We never told Mom about that day. </i>

221
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:18,889
<i>And that bothered me a lot. </i>

222
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:23,060
Comb that hair back for you.

223
00:18:23,469 --> 00:18:26,370
Get you to look like a real man here. Okay.

224
00:18:27,973 --> 00:18:30,237
Look at you. Look at this hair.

225
00:18:36,315 --> 00:18:39,876
I now pronounce you man and wife.
You may kiss the bride.

226
00:18:48,193 --> 00:18:51,356
<i>In the summer of 1969,</i>
<i>we moved to the suburbs... </i>

227
00:18:51,864 --> 00:18:55,527
<i>where everybody had a house, a car,</i>
<i>and two-and-a-half kids. </i>

228
00:18:55,734 --> 00:18:58,032
<i>So we figured we fit in really good... </i>

229
00:18:58,103 --> 00:19:01,197
<i>because with Shane,</i>
<i>that's exactly what we were. </i>

230
00:19:01,740 --> 00:19:04,675
Check this out. Hi! Ask who they are.

231
00:19:05,110 --> 00:19:07,374
- Hey, who are you?
- Yeah, who are you?

232
00:19:09,014 --> 00:19:10,038
Who's that?

233
00:19:10,115 --> 00:19:13,243
<i>But The King bought the house</i>
<i>from a family named the Marshals. </i>

234
00:19:13,318 --> 00:19:16,845
<i>And there were two boys about our ages</i>
<i>living in it when it got sold. </i>

235
00:19:16,922 --> 00:19:20,221
They kicked out the Marshals?
Hey, they kicked out the Marshals.

236
00:19:20,292 --> 00:19:22,886
<i>Me and Bobby never kicked anyone</i>
<i>out of anywhere. </i>

237
00:19:22,961 --> 00:19:27,898
<i>But for some reason, the rest of the kids</i>
<i>on the block always said we did. </i>

238
00:19:28,967 --> 00:19:31,060
Come on, out of the way.

239
00:19:31,336 --> 00:19:32,928
We need the key.

240
00:19:33,505 --> 00:19:37,134
Yes, the key! Watch out, Shane.

241
00:19:37,876 --> 00:19:41,334
Give me a kiss. I love you guys.

242
00:19:46,385 --> 00:19:50,446
<i>It was there, when all of Mom's prayers</i>
<i>were just about answered... </i>

243
00:19:50,622 --> 00:19:55,321
<i>when everything seemed like it would be</i>
<i>happy and good for the rest of our lives... </i>

244
00:19:55,694 --> 00:19:57,719
<i>that it really all began. </i>

245
00:20:06,705 --> 00:20:09,367
It's official now. Sold.

246
00:20:09,575 --> 00:20:12,305
- It's official now.
- Great, Jack. It's official.

247
00:20:14,012 --> 00:20:15,536
Yes, it's ours!

248
00:20:20,319 --> 00:20:23,447
Hi, welcome to the neighborhood.
How y'all doing?

249
00:20:26,992 --> 00:20:29,517
- Come on, let's go.
- Hi.

250
00:20:31,129 --> 00:20:32,494
- Hi, guys.
- Hi.

251
00:20:32,564 --> 00:20:35,260
- What's your name?
- I'm Mike and that's Bobby.

252
00:20:35,667 --> 00:20:38,500
- This is our dog, Shane.
- Hi, how do you do?

253
00:20:38,637 --> 00:20:42,767
- I'm Jim Daugherty from the Sheriff's office.
- Hi, I'm Mary Mackenzie.

254
00:20:52,918 --> 00:20:55,887
- Come on!
- I'm coming.

255
00:20:59,891 --> 00:21:02,382
Mom, can me and Bobby go exploring?

256
00:21:03,895 --> 00:21:06,329
Is your room put away?

257
00:21:06,632 --> 00:21:09,294
- We'll check.
- That's what I thought.

258
00:21:22,481 --> 00:21:25,245
- Mike, get me out of here.
- Get out.

259
00:21:25,817 --> 00:21:27,148
Come on, let's go!

260
00:21:27,219 --> 00:21:29,050
We checked. It's clean.

261
00:21:29,121 --> 00:21:32,955
Are you kidding me?
You've only been in there for 27 seconds.

262
00:21:33,425 --> 00:21:35,586
Mikey, Bobby, come on.

263
00:21:36,461 --> 00:21:37,826
All right!

264
00:21:38,930 --> 00:21:40,591
Don't scratch it.

265
00:21:41,433 --> 00:21:43,833
- Wow!
- I bet there's some secret entrances.

266
00:21:43,902 --> 00:21:46,268
The Marshall kids
must have built it as a fort.

267
00:21:46,338 --> 00:21:48,203
- Anything?
- No, nothing.

268
00:21:48,674 --> 00:21:52,337
Come on, Bobby. This must be it.

269
00:22:00,152 --> 00:22:02,620
Shane, don't go in there! No!

270
00:22:13,098 --> 00:22:14,759
It's a turtle.

271
00:22:15,534 --> 00:22:17,832
That's what I was going to say.

272
00:22:19,838 --> 00:22:21,430
Look at that chain.

273
00:22:21,506 --> 00:22:24,532
He must have busted it
and climbed into the clubhouse.

274
00:22:24,609 --> 00:22:27,271
- We gotta name him.
- Yeah, but what?

275
00:22:31,016 --> 00:22:34,816
- Good one, Shane. Samson.
- Samson? Why?

276
00:22:35,187 --> 00:22:38,588
Hey, stay back.
'Cause he was so strong to break the chain.

277
00:22:38,657 --> 00:22:41,854
Yeah, great! Samson. Welcome to the family.

278
00:22:42,561 --> 00:22:44,791
Back in your old home, Samson.

279
00:22:46,298 --> 00:22:49,358
Carefully put him down. Ready?
One, two, three.

280
00:22:54,373 --> 00:22:55,601
What's that?

281
00:22:57,142 --> 00:22:58,871
Look at this, Bobby.

282
00:22:59,478 --> 00:23:01,241
This board's loose.

283
00:23:08,453 --> 00:23:10,284
It's a coffee can.

284
00:23:12,624 --> 00:23:15,684
- Nothing in here. Wait.
- It's a bank.

285
00:23:15,761 --> 00:23:18,457
Nothing else under here
but a bunch of spiders.

286
00:23:18,964 --> 00:23:22,957
Darn, it's empty.
Bobby, we can stash money in this thing.

287
00:23:25,237 --> 00:23:29,469
- Don't tell anybody about this, okay?
- I swear. Pinkie promise.

288
00:23:40,986 --> 00:23:43,819
I'm telling you,
you're not supposed to pick your nose.

289
00:23:43,889 --> 00:23:45,789
Your brains will fall out.

290
00:23:45,857 --> 00:23:47,848
- Will not.
- Will so.

291
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:51,323
You'll make a hole in your head
and your brains will fall out.

292
00:23:51,396 --> 00:23:54,263
- Will not.
- Yeah? Let's go ask Mom.

293
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:57,234
- Okay, let's ask her.
- Fine.

294
00:24:37,843 --> 00:24:40,539
- Mom, the room's clean.
- Clothes are washed and folded.

295
00:24:40,612 --> 00:24:42,580
- Fed Samson and Shane.
- Picked the poop up.

296
00:24:42,647 --> 00:24:44,979
- And the grass is watered.
- Okay.

297
00:24:45,584 --> 00:24:47,984
- Guys.
- Yes, Mom?

298
00:24:48,053 --> 00:24:51,045
I want you to be back here
before your dad gets home.

299
00:24:51,122 --> 00:24:54,523
And I have to work double shifts
all summer long...

300
00:24:54,593 --> 00:24:57,426
- so I don't want you out too late.
- Okay.

301
00:24:58,263 --> 00:24:59,457
Guys.

302
00:25:00,265 --> 00:25:02,130
Yes, Mom, what is it?

303
00:25:03,468 --> 00:25:04,799
Nothing.

304
00:25:08,974 --> 00:25:10,339
I love you.

305
00:25:11,510 --> 00:25:13,375
We love you, too, Mom.

306
00:25:21,553 --> 00:25:24,044
- Hi, how are you?
- Hi!

307
00:25:25,991 --> 00:25:29,188
<i>Before anybody ever grows up,</i>
<i>there are magical things... </i>

308
00:25:29,261 --> 00:25:31,593
<i>impossible for adults, that can still happen. </i>

309
00:25:31,663 --> 00:25:35,292
<i>The reason these things</i>
<i>are lost to the grown-up world is simple. </i>

310
00:25:35,367 --> 00:25:38,734
<i>In the quick second between the age of 12</i>
<i>and your 13th birthday... </i>

311
00:25:38,803 --> 00:25:41,533
<i>the great secrets to them all</i>
<i>are replaced in your mind... </i>

312
00:25:41,606 --> 00:25:43,870
<i>with thoughts of the opposite sex. </i>

313
00:25:47,712 --> 00:25:49,839
- Say, "Uncle. "
- Uncle.

314
00:25:49,915 --> 00:25:51,143
- Give?
- Uncle.

315
00:25:51,716 --> 00:25:55,516
<i>There are seven of these lost</i>
<i>secret fascinations and abilities. </i>

316
00:25:56,054 --> 00:25:58,648
<i>They are: That animals can talk. </i>

317
00:26:02,661 --> 00:26:05,494
<i>Your favorite blanket</i>
<i>is woven from a fabric so mighty... </i>

318
00:26:05,564 --> 00:26:09,796
<i>that once pulled over your head,</i>
<i>it becomes an impenetrable force field. </i>

319
00:26:11,469 --> 00:26:12,800
Great.

320
00:26:15,607 --> 00:26:18,599
<i>Nothing is too heavy to lift,</i>
<i>with the aid of a cape. </i>

321
00:26:20,445 --> 00:26:23,141
Mikey, you did it. Wow!

322
00:26:24,182 --> 00:26:28,414
<i>Your hand, held forefinger out</i>
<i>and thumbs up, actually fires bullets. </i>

323
00:26:31,423 --> 00:26:32,481
Hurry.

324
00:26:37,562 --> 00:26:40,998
<i>Jumping from any height with an umbrella</i>
<i>is completely safe. </i>

325
00:26:43,668 --> 00:26:45,363
You okay?

326
00:26:45,437 --> 00:26:47,371
I did it, Mike. I flew.

327
00:26:52,243 --> 00:26:56,805
<i>Monsters exist,</i>
<i>that can both be seen and done battle with. </i>

328
00:26:56,881 --> 00:26:58,906
One, two, three!

329
00:27:08,026 --> 00:27:11,792
<i>And the greatest,</i>
<i>most special and regrettable loss of all:</i>

330
00:27:12,397 --> 00:27:14,194
<i>The ability to fly. </i>

331
00:27:21,039 --> 00:27:23,701
<i>From what we'd heard around</i>
<i>about that kid Fisher... </i>

332
00:27:23,775 --> 00:27:27,438
<i>and what he'd done 10 years</i>
<i>before we'd moved into the neighborhood... </i>

333
00:27:27,512 --> 00:27:29,446
<i>we knew the second we saw it. </i>

334
00:27:29,514 --> 00:27:31,414
That must be the place.

335
00:27:31,549 --> 00:27:33,710
Truly. Could be killed.

336
00:27:34,452 --> 00:27:37,717
<i>That's why they called that kid Fisher</i>
<i>a legend... </i>

337
00:27:37,922 --> 00:27:41,187
<i>because he did the greatest thing</i>
<i>anybody's ever heard of. </i>

338
00:27:41,493 --> 00:27:43,654
- He wasn't that great.
- What do you mean?

339
00:27:43,728 --> 00:27:45,958
- He got killed, didn't he?
- No, he didn't.

340
00:27:46,031 --> 00:27:47,658
- Yeah, he did.
- No, he didn't.

341
00:27:47,732 --> 00:27:51,190
Yeah, he did. Look at that jump.
You know, at the barn?

342
00:27:52,270 --> 00:27:55,296
It's a long way down, probably 2 miles.

343
00:27:55,674 --> 00:27:57,665
Probably did a good try.

344
00:27:58,510 --> 00:28:00,375
He just did it wrong.

345
00:28:01,546 --> 00:28:05,607
- We should do an expedition up there.
- Yeah, it's probably cool up there.

346
00:28:06,951 --> 00:28:09,112
- Not today, though.
- Yeah, not today.

347
00:28:09,187 --> 00:28:10,814
Nah, too busy.

348
00:28:13,391 --> 00:28:14,619
We will...

349
00:28:15,994 --> 00:28:17,120
later.

350
00:28:29,741 --> 00:28:31,732
Please, help.

351
00:28:33,278 --> 00:28:34,370
Stop.

352
00:28:39,250 --> 00:28:41,810
Please, don't. Help.

353
00:28:52,764 --> 00:28:55,858
No, don't! Please stop.

354
00:28:56,101 --> 00:28:58,729
- No, don't do it! Stop.
- Oh, my God. Bobby.

355
00:29:00,004 --> 00:29:01,528
Bobby, it's me.

356
00:29:07,112 --> 00:29:08,636
It's me, Bobby.

357
00:29:09,180 --> 00:29:11,808
What happened to your back?

358
00:29:13,885 --> 00:29:15,147
Oh, God.

359
00:29:16,755 --> 00:29:18,882
Don't you ever tell Mom, Mike.

360
00:29:19,524 --> 00:29:21,048
Don't you ever.

361
00:29:22,060 --> 00:29:23,925
- Promise?
- I promise.

362
00:29:27,499 --> 00:29:29,228
What was the dream?

363
00:29:30,101 --> 00:29:32,001
What was the nightmare about?

364
00:29:34,806 --> 00:29:38,401
- You swear you won't tell Mom?
- Yeah.

365
00:29:40,645 --> 00:29:44,945
The King, he was chasing me
and I couldn't get away.

366
00:29:46,217 --> 00:29:48,617
Did he do that to your back?

367
00:29:50,388 --> 00:29:52,720
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

368
00:29:57,729 --> 00:30:01,460
I was afraid you'd tell Mom.
She's happy now.

369
00:30:03,067 --> 00:30:07,231
<i>At that moment,</i>
<i>I realized that Bobby was my responsibility. </i>

370
00:30:08,807 --> 00:30:11,503
<i>I had to think up some way to help him. </i>

371
00:30:19,884 --> 00:30:22,614
<i>I made sure we left our house</i>
<i>when the sun came up... </i>

372
00:30:22,687 --> 00:30:25,281
<i>and we never went home till just after dark. </i>

373
00:30:25,623 --> 00:30:28,285
<i>That way,</i>
<i>Bobby could avoid The King all day. </i>

374
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:31,856
<i>So we spent all our time expeditioning. </i>

375
00:30:35,600 --> 00:30:37,192
Come on.

376
00:30:38,469 --> 00:30:40,130
Come here, frog.

377
00:30:41,339 --> 00:30:44,137
- Okay, we got one.
- We got two, you mean.

378
00:30:44,209 --> 00:30:47,201
- Open it for me, will you?
- Okay.

379
00:31:03,027 --> 00:31:05,188
<i>We knew we were in trouble instantly... </i>

380
00:31:05,263 --> 00:31:09,290
<i>the way kids know they're in for it</i>
<i>when bigger kids appear in front of them. </i>

381
00:31:09,367 --> 00:31:13,963
<i>It's a sixth sense that you never lose. </i>
<i>And we knew we were as good as dead. </i>

382
00:31:14,038 --> 00:31:16,097
You're dead. You're both dead.

383
00:31:28,253 --> 00:31:31,916
- Frogs?
- We're the only ones who can catch frogs.

384
00:31:31,990 --> 00:31:34,584
Yeah, you need Victor's permission
to go in the pipe.

385
00:31:34,659 --> 00:31:38,095
You need Victor's permission
for everything around here, sissies.

386
00:31:38,162 --> 00:31:39,220
It ain't your pipe.

387
00:31:40,899 --> 00:31:42,696
You're both dead.

388
00:31:45,236 --> 00:31:47,534
All right. Tell your mutt to stay there, man.

389
00:31:47,605 --> 00:31:50,506
He ain't a mutt.
He's a killer German shepherd attack dog.

390
00:31:50,575 --> 00:31:53,066
And if you move any closer, he'll kill you.

391
00:31:54,445 --> 00:31:57,243
Just tell him to cool down.
Tell him to stay there, all right?

392
00:31:57,315 --> 00:32:00,045
- Say, "Please. "
- Say, "Pretty please. "

393
00:32:00,451 --> 00:32:02,442
- Kiss my butt.
- Yeah.

394
00:32:03,254 --> 00:32:05,654
Okay, Shane. Kill!

395
00:32:09,627 --> 00:32:12,460
You're dead meat. Dead as a doornail.

396
00:32:12,530 --> 00:32:14,725
Good boy, Shane. Good going.

397
00:32:15,833 --> 00:32:17,061
Come on.

398
00:32:22,807 --> 00:32:24,707
- Hi, guys.
- Hi, Mom.

399
00:32:24,776 --> 00:32:26,300
What's cooking?

400
00:32:30,982 --> 00:32:33,212
Guys, who stepped in what here?

401
00:32:34,619 --> 00:32:36,314
- It wasn't me.
- Me, either.

402
00:32:36,387 --> 00:32:38,218
- Where were you?
- We were exploring.

403
00:32:38,289 --> 00:32:39,950
- Where?
- Sewers.

404
00:32:41,759 --> 00:32:43,386
That is just disgusting!

405
00:32:47,398 --> 00:32:50,424
It's perfect. Okay, come on. Big boys first.

406
00:32:50,501 --> 00:32:53,561
- Mom, I can do it myself.
- I'll help you. You're first.

407
00:32:53,638 --> 00:32:55,663
- I can do it myself.
- Come on.

408
00:32:59,377 --> 00:33:01,208
You guys are nuts!

409
00:33:01,279 --> 00:33:04,339
I have no time for games.
I have to go to work.

410
00:33:04,716 --> 00:33:06,707
I can't believe you guys!

411
00:33:07,118 --> 00:33:10,417
Finish your baths.
All filthy clothes in the wash.

412
00:33:10,488 --> 00:33:12,149
I'm going to work.

413
00:33:13,858 --> 00:33:15,325
Thanks, Mike.

414
00:33:26,938 --> 00:33:30,339
Hi, honey. Good night. Goodbye. I love you.

415
00:34:01,205 --> 00:34:03,503
It's coming down.

416
00:34:04,776 --> 00:34:05,765
I know.

417
00:34:20,758 --> 00:34:23,989
<i>It's alive. He's moving. He's alive. </i>

418
00:34:24,729 --> 00:34:26,162
<i>It's alive!</i>

419
00:34:31,002 --> 00:34:32,833
<i>In the name of God!</i>

420
00:34:49,387 --> 00:34:51,719
What are you doing up? Go to bed.

421
00:34:53,524 --> 00:34:56,755
Not you. Bobby, come here.
Mikey, you go to bed.

422
00:34:56,828 --> 00:34:58,420
- Bobby, come here.
- But I want to...

423
00:34:58,496 --> 00:35:01,431
Go to bed! Come here, Bobby.

424
00:35:02,700 --> 00:35:04,065
Come here!

425
00:35:09,707 --> 00:35:13,006
What did I tell you?
Why don't you listen to me?

426
00:35:13,077 --> 00:35:16,308
Why don't you ever listen
to what I'm telling you to do?

427
00:35:19,984 --> 00:35:22,452
Get to bed, you little son of a bitch!

428
00:35:31,629 --> 00:35:34,325
We can't stay up so late anymore.

429
00:38:13,391 --> 00:38:16,224
- Are you real?
- Sure.

430
00:38:17,094 --> 00:38:18,755
Touch my nose.

431
00:38:24,635 --> 00:38:26,660
But how did you get here?

432
00:38:29,807 --> 00:38:31,570
The window was open.

433
00:38:34,011 --> 00:38:36,036
Michael, it's getting worse.

434
00:38:39,083 --> 00:38:42,018
Why is this happening to Bobby
and not to me?

435
00:38:42,086 --> 00:38:44,611
Because Bobby cannot fight back.

436
00:38:45,222 --> 00:38:48,885
But you can. You have to help him.

437
00:38:50,294 --> 00:38:52,421
But I don't know what to do.

438
00:38:52,663 --> 00:38:55,826
I can't tell Mom. I can't tell anyone.

439
00:38:56,233 --> 00:38:59,725
- I can't break my promise to him.
- Keep your promise...

440
00:39:00,404 --> 00:39:02,497
but listen to Bobby.

441
00:39:02,573 --> 00:39:05,201
Bobby already has the answer.

442
00:39:05,276 --> 00:39:07,676
It is for you to help him find it.

443
00:39:09,213 --> 00:39:11,147
Good night, Michael.

444
00:39:12,350 --> 00:39:14,284
Good night, Bobby.

445
00:39:16,954 --> 00:39:18,683
Good night, buffalo.

446
00:39:19,990 --> 00:39:22,185
<i>The dream had given me a strength... </i>

447
00:39:22,827 --> 00:39:24,920
<i>a sudden sense of purpose. </i>

448
00:39:31,669 --> 00:39:34,934
- Look, a house!
- Cool!

449
00:39:41,846 --> 00:39:43,939
- You okay?
- Open her up.

450
00:39:47,852 --> 00:39:49,217
Cool.

451
00:39:54,058 --> 00:39:55,616
An engine!

452
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:59,459
Like from an airplane or a grass cutter.

453
00:40:01,332 --> 00:40:03,129
You mean a lawn mower.

454
00:40:03,601 --> 00:40:05,660
Yeah. Groovy.

455
00:40:06,537 --> 00:40:08,596
But, Mike, how do we get it?

456
00:40:11,509 --> 00:40:12,908
We don't.

457
00:40:14,845 --> 00:40:16,642
We shouldn't, anyway.

458
00:40:16,914 --> 00:40:19,576
Come on, Shane. It ain't ours.

459
00:40:21,519 --> 00:40:25,979
Mike, it's been in there a million years.
The owner's probably dead.

460
00:40:27,291 --> 00:40:31,318
Yeah, probably.
Wait a sec. What do we need it for?

461
00:40:35,800 --> 00:40:37,734
Don't know yet.

462
00:40:39,136 --> 00:40:40,330
What?

463
00:40:40,738 --> 00:40:42,228
Nothing.

464
00:40:53,717 --> 00:40:57,710
- Oh, no! The Flyer!
- Shane, get it!

465
00:40:57,822 --> 00:41:01,952
- Hurry up, Mike. It's trying to get away.
- Get it, Shane!

466
00:41:03,027 --> 00:41:04,892
Come on, Shane! Get it!

467
00:41:18,342 --> 00:41:20,435
- Not too fast.
