<i>Your son, Mike. </i>

948
01:28:14,856 --> 01:28:16,153
Okay.

949
01:28:29,804 --> 01:28:31,772
6:45. Let's go.

950
01:29:18,786 --> 01:29:21,277
<i>No other kids in the history of the world... </i>

951
01:29:21,356 --> 01:29:23,290
<i>had ever had a better idea. </i>

952
01:29:26,627 --> 01:29:28,891
<i>And if they did, they never built it. </i>

953
01:29:33,067 --> 01:29:37,003
<i>The Radio Flyer was going to soar. </i>

954
01:29:40,375 --> 01:29:42,104
<i>Suddenly it became clear to me... </i>

955
01:29:42,176 --> 01:29:44,701
<i>why Bobby always got those faraway looks</i>
<i>in his eyes... </i>

956
01:29:44,779 --> 01:29:47,270
<i>whenever he looked at the Radio Flyer. </i>

957
01:29:48,082 --> 01:29:50,380
<i>He had known something I didn't. </i>

958
01:29:51,819 --> 01:29:54,379
<i>He had known the true potential</i>
<i>of the wagon. </i>

959
01:29:54,455 --> 01:29:59,051
<i>He could see right through the metal of it</i>
<i>and imagine the way it should have been. </i>

960
01:30:00,628 --> 01:30:05,065
<i>See, it wasn't just the bright red paint,</i>
<i>or the logo that was written on it... </i>

961
01:30:05,133 --> 01:30:08,591
<i>so it looked like the words were gonna fly</i>
<i>right off the sides. </i>

962
01:30:09,504 --> 01:30:11,904
<i>It was what the wagon represented. </i>

963
01:30:13,374 --> 01:30:15,638
<i>It meant escape. </i>

964
01:30:18,179 --> 01:30:20,807
<i>Who The King of terrors couldn't see... </i>

965
01:30:21,382 --> 01:30:23,816
<i>who he couldn't look into the soul of... </i>

966
01:30:23,985 --> 01:30:26,647
<i>and who he couldn't get his hands on... </i>

967
01:30:26,854 --> 01:30:28,378
<i>he couldn't hurt. </i>

968
01:30:29,724 --> 01:30:31,589
<i>Bobby was going away... </i>

969
01:30:31,893 --> 01:30:35,624
<i>to faraway places</i>
<i>where The King could never hurt him again. </i>

970
01:30:37,031 --> 01:30:39,522
<i>That was what the Flyer was for. </i>

971
01:30:42,336 --> 01:30:45,032
<i>And that pretty much was the Big Idea. </i>

972
01:31:03,858 --> 01:31:05,621
God damn it!

973
01:31:40,461 --> 01:31:43,624
- Fill her up, please.
- With Super.

974
01:32:11,025 --> 01:32:14,085
If there's anything left of her
halfway down...

975
01:32:14,929 --> 01:32:16,521
you got a chance.

976
01:32:20,301 --> 01:32:23,828
At the bottom, just before you grab air...

977
01:32:24,472 --> 01:32:27,635
ease off. Don't pull up. You'll stall out.

978
01:32:29,277 --> 01:32:30,904
The angle's too great.

979
01:32:32,280 --> 01:32:33,577
You got it?

980
01:32:59,507 --> 01:33:00,872
Here.

981
01:33:18,893 --> 01:33:20,520
Fish, telephone.

982
01:33:42,483 --> 01:33:44,041
Good luck, kid.

983
01:34:04,572 --> 01:34:07,370
<i>Fisher's flight had been doomed</i>
<i>from the beginning... </i>

984
01:34:07,441 --> 01:34:10,239
<i>because he tried it way after</i>
<i>he lost all the knowledge... </i>

985
01:34:10,311 --> 01:34:12,939
<i>of the seven great abilities and fascinations. </i>

986
01:34:13,147 --> 01:34:16,048
<i>You see, he was 14.</i>

987
01:34:18,719 --> 01:34:20,983
Here you go. This one's on the house.

988
01:34:22,223 --> 01:34:23,622
Pick it up, Shirley.

989
01:34:23,691 --> 01:34:26,421
It's kind of slow.
Why don't one of you go home?

990
01:34:26,827 --> 01:34:29,887
- I'll stay.
- Yeah. Thanks.

991
01:34:31,666 --> 01:34:32,690
Groovy.

992
01:34:33,267 --> 01:34:36,600
- It's been swell.
- Good night, Mary.

993
01:35:05,499 --> 01:35:07,330
She's beautiful.

994
01:35:11,038 --> 01:35:12,596
She's amazing.

995
01:35:39,467 --> 01:35:42,459
I told those guys to stay off of that hill.

996
01:36:20,508 --> 01:36:23,966
Too risky. Better wait till they all take off.

997
01:36:30,651 --> 01:36:32,516
What's going on here?

998
01:36:33,354 --> 01:36:36,517
Answer me. I'm home. Hello?

999
01:36:42,863 --> 01:36:44,194
Come on.

1000
01:36:50,137 --> 01:36:54,301
<i>Dear Mom, me and Bobby went to</i>
<i>The Wishing Spot with the Radio Flyer. </i>

1001
01:36:54,375 --> 01:36:58,038
<i>I will be back, but Bobby won't. </i>
<i>Please don't get mad. </i>

1002
01:36:58,879 --> 01:37:02,246
<i>We took Samson and Shane, too. </i>
<i>Your son, Mike. </i>

1003
01:37:08,522 --> 01:37:12,083
That's one, Bobby.
There's only two more to go.

1004
01:37:14,428 --> 01:37:16,555
You gotta get ready. Come on.

1005
01:37:19,099 --> 01:37:20,726
You promised me!

1006
01:37:30,444 --> 01:37:33,174
There's stamps in there
for you to send me the postcards.

1007
01:37:33,247 --> 01:37:36,011
- You'd better send them to us.
- Thanks, Mike.

1008
01:37:41,255 --> 01:37:42,984
Damn that music!

1009
01:37:50,197 --> 01:37:53,496
Please, I need to speak to Officer Daugherty
right away.

1010
01:37:58,272 --> 01:37:59,739
What are you doing?

1011
01:38:01,208 --> 01:38:03,768
No, Mike, that's your favorite jacket.

1012
01:38:06,213 --> 01:38:07,202
Come on.

1013
01:38:07,281 --> 01:38:09,681
It's yours now. You gotta keep warm.

1014
01:38:32,940 --> 01:38:35,841
I want to go, too. I want to go.

1015
01:38:37,378 --> 01:38:40,870
You can't. You gotta stay home
and take care of Mom.

1016
01:38:43,350 --> 01:38:45,284
Bobby, I'm gonna miss you.

1017
01:38:47,488 --> 01:38:49,752
I wanna be with you.

1018
01:38:55,863 --> 01:38:57,490
You gotta get ready.

1019
01:39:05,606 --> 01:39:09,440
So long, Shane. I love you.
Take care of Bobby.

1020
01:39:16,984 --> 01:39:19,817
Samson, be a good turtle. Have a good ride.

1021
01:39:25,592 --> 01:39:29,528
Mike, the third one took off. We gotta go.

1022
01:39:35,970 --> 01:39:38,837
Hang on, Bobby.
I'm gonna get that rock out.

1023
01:39:42,109 --> 01:39:45,169
Come on! I can't get this thing loose.

1024
01:39:47,648 --> 01:39:48,945
Come on!

1025
01:39:50,484 --> 01:39:52,645
You little son of a bitch!

1026
01:40:03,797 --> 01:40:05,526
Free the wheel.

1027
01:40:11,972 --> 01:40:13,701
Hang on, Bobby!

1028
01:40:15,776 --> 01:40:17,539
Start it, Mike!

1029
01:40:19,013 --> 01:40:20,913
Hang on!

1030
01:40:21,215 --> 01:40:23,206
- I got it!
- Pull the cord!

1031
01:40:23,851 --> 01:40:26,046
- I got it!
- I love you, Mike.

1032
01:40:26,120 --> 01:40:27,519
I love you, Bobby.

1033
01:40:50,511 --> 01:40:54,277
Mike, I'm in the slot. Do you read me?

1034
01:40:57,851 --> 01:41:00,319
- Can you hear me?
<i>- I'm in the slot, Mike!</i>

1035
01:41:28,582 --> 01:41:31,107
Mike, I'm falling. She's going down.

1036
01:41:31,952 --> 01:41:33,317
<i>Do you read me?</i>

1037
01:41:33,387 --> 01:41:35,252
<i>Listen to me. The Cox engines. </i>

1038
01:41:35,322 --> 01:41:38,450
The auxiliaries, the thing above your head.
Pull it, now!

1039
01:41:49,570 --> 01:41:51,868
<i>Mike, I'm flying!</i>

1040
01:41:51,939 --> 01:41:55,466
He's flying. You're flying, Bobby. I knew it.

1041
01:41:58,245 --> 01:42:01,373
<i>I'm trying to turn her, Mike,</i>
<i>but there's a lot of wind. </i>

1042
01:42:02,149 --> 01:42:05,175
Bobby, I see you.
You're right over the airport.

1043
01:42:06,687 --> 01:42:09,212
<i>Mike, can you hear me?</i>

1044
01:42:09,623 --> 01:42:12,956
<i>Take care of Shane. Take care of Mom. </i>

1045
01:42:14,027 --> 01:42:16,928
<i>Goodbye, Mike. I love you. </i>

1046
01:42:19,833 --> 01:42:21,323
Goodbye, Bob.

1047
01:42:56,103 --> 01:42:57,263
There.

1048
01:43:05,445 --> 01:43:06,912
Where's Bobby?

1049
01:43:17,024 --> 01:43:18,013
You're done.

1050
01:43:20,194 --> 01:43:22,128
Mikey, where's Bobby?

1051
01:43:23,463 --> 01:43:25,522
- Mike, where's your brother?
- Mom.

1052
01:43:28,669 --> 01:43:31,729
What? Michael, where is he?

1053
01:43:35,108 --> 01:43:37,099
He made it, Mom.

1054
01:43:37,811 --> 01:43:39,608
What are you talking about?

1055
01:43:40,314 --> 01:43:42,111
He's gone, Mom.

1056
01:43:47,621 --> 01:43:49,350
Where is he?

1057
01:43:50,057 --> 01:43:52,821
Like Bobby said, it's gonna be okay now.

1058
01:43:53,694 --> 01:43:55,059
He's safe.

1059
01:43:57,030 --> 01:43:58,497
He's okay now.

1060
01:44:10,444 --> 01:44:14,244
<i>However many times I tried</i>
<i>explaining to Mom what had happened... </i>

1061
01:44:14,414 --> 01:44:19,078
<i>being grown up, she could never recapture</i>
<i>the frame of mind needed to understand. </i>

1062
01:44:19,886 --> 01:44:23,481
<i>But being our mom,</i>
<i>she never stopped looking. </i>

1063
01:44:25,025 --> 01:44:28,791
<i>Never, that is,</i>
<i>until the day I ran home from school... </i>

1064
01:44:28,862 --> 01:44:31,797
<i>and all her fears and worries</i>
<i>were laid to rest. </i>

1065
01:44:33,634 --> 01:44:36,159
<i>The day I got the first postcard. </i>

1066
01:44:36,470 --> 01:44:38,904
Mom, look!

1067
01:44:54,721 --> 01:44:57,019
It came, Mom.

1068
01:44:57,391 --> 01:44:59,916
<i>Dear Mom and Mike, I am fine. </i>

1069
01:44:59,993 --> 01:45:03,360
<i>I hope you are, too. The Flyer works great. </i>

1070
01:45:03,864 --> 01:45:08,062
<i>I scared the buffalo, flying too low. </i>
<i>But Geronimo Bill was nice. </i>

1071
01:45:09,069 --> 01:45:11,299
<i>I love you. Bobby. </i>

1072
01:45:20,514 --> 01:45:23,745
I told you, Mom. I told you he'd write.

1073
01:45:29,423 --> 01:45:32,688
<i>Time passed, and I grew up,</i>
<i>and I went to college. </i>

1074
01:45:32,959 --> 01:45:37,658
<i>But I never completely lost all knowledge</i>
<i>of the seven great abilities and fascinations. </i>

1075
01:45:38,231 --> 01:45:40,859
<i>Every time I felt them slipping away... </i>

1076
01:45:41,268 --> 01:45:43,202
<i>I got another postcard. </i>

1077
01:45:43,904 --> 01:45:46,065
<i>Bobby traveled all over the world... </i>

1078
01:45:46,139 --> 01:45:49,597
<i>and visited places we dreamed</i>
<i>about visiting when we were kids. </i>

1079
01:45:49,810 --> 01:45:53,143
<i>You see, in time, he grew up to be... </i>

1080
01:45:53,513 --> 01:45:55,811
<i>exactly what he was born to be:</i>

1081
01:45:57,551 --> 01:45:58,950
<i>A flyer. </i>

1082
01:46:25,846 --> 01:46:30,613
Do you guys understand what I meant about
history being in the mind of the teller now?

1083
01:46:30,917 --> 01:46:32,544
I think so.

1084
01:46:34,254 --> 01:46:35,448
Good.

1085
01:46:37,224 --> 01:46:39,624
'Cause that's how I remember him.

1086
01:46:42,996 --> 01:46:45,157
Dad, can we ask you a question?

1087
01:46:46,433 --> 01:46:47,661
Yeah, sure.

1088
01:46:49,369 --> 01:46:51,496
Is that where we got Samson?

1089
01:46:55,776 --> 01:46:59,143
Yeah, that's right.
That's exactly where we got him.

1090
01:46:59,413 --> 01:47:03,349
Really? You promise? You pinkie promise?

1091
01:47:09,790 --> 01:47:11,724
I pinkie promise.

1092
01:47:18,765 --> 01:47:20,198
You see...

1093
01:47:20,267 --> 01:47:24,294
that's what makes a promise
such a big deal.

1094
01:47:25,972 --> 01:47:29,100
Once you make it, it'll last forever.

1095
01:47:39,101 --> 01:47:41,901
